With a heavy Guyanese influence, this place is amazing for experience folks of Caribbean background that likes the company of other mature people. Their karaoke night is especially wonderful. You will hear Caribbean classics that remind you of the blissful moments sometimes dating back to the 70s and 80s. The audience is very supportive and you will love it. They also serve cutters(food when drinking). The DJ Stacey is very fun and gives off amazing energy whether singing along in karaoke or when mixing music. Definitely would recommend this place!
